# AMR-GigaWord 200k

# ::id 0 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok a possible us attack on iraq will have minimal impact on the country 's tourism as the war will be restricted in the middle east , the tourism authority of thailand -lrb- tat -rrb- said in a report thursday .
# ::alignments
(s / say-01
      :ARG0 (a / authority
            :topic (t / tourism)
            :mod (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Thailand")))
      :ARG1 (p / possible-01
            :ARG1 (ii / impact-01
                  :ARG0 (a2 / attack-01
                        :ARG0 (w / we)
                        :ARG1 (c2 / country
                              :name (n2 / name
                                    :op1 "Iraq")))
                  :ARG1 (t2 / tourism
                        :poss c2)
                  :ARG1-of (m / minimal-02)
                  :ARG1-of (c3 / cause-01
                        :ARG0 (r / restrict-01
                              :ARG1 (w2 / war-01)
                              :location (w3 / world-region
                                    :name (n3 / name
                                          :op1 "Middle"
                                          :op2 "East"))))))
      :medium (r2 / report
            :time (d / date-entity
                  :weekday (t3 / thursday))))

# ::id 1 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok former british prime minister harold wilson was buried tuesday in a simply ceremony on one of the scilly isles off the coast off southwest england .
# ::alignments
(b / bury-01
      :ARG1 (p / person
            :name (n / name
                  :op1 "Harold"
                  :op2 " wilson")
            :ARG0-of (h / have-org-role-91
                  :ARG1 (c / country
                        :name (n2 / name
                              :op1 "Great"
                              :op2 "Britain"))
                  :ARG2 (m / minister
                        :mod (p2 / prime))
                  :time (f / former)))
      :time (d / date-entity
            :weekday (t / tuesday))
      :location (ii / island
            :quant 1
            :ARG1-of (ii2 / include-91
                  :ARG2 (ii3 / island
                        :mod (s / scilly)))
            :location (o / off
                  :op1 (c2 / coast
                        :location (c3 / country-region
                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "Southwest"
                                    :op2 "England")))))
      :manner (c4 / ceremony
            :ARG1-of (s2 / simple-02)))

# ::id 2 ::amr-annotator ISI-AMR-01 ::preferred
# ::tok african leaders gathered to address pressing issues concerning political stability and socio-economic development in the continent as the ##nd organization of african unity -lrb- oau -rrb- summit opened here today .
# ::alignments
(g / gather-03
      :ARG0 (p / person

                  :ARG1 (c / continent
                        :name (n / name
                              :op1 "Africa"))))
      :purpose (a / address-02
            :ARG0 p
            :ARG1 (ii / issue-02
                  :ARG0-of (p2 / press-01)
                  :topic (a2 / and
                        :op1 (s / stable-03
                              :ARG1 (p3 / politics))
                        :op2 (d / develop-02
                              :ARG1 (e / economy
                                    :mod (s2 / society)))
                        :location c)))
      :time (o / open-02
            :ARG1 (o2 / organization
                  :name n
                  :op1 "Unite"
                  :op2 "Against"
                  :op3 "Africa"
                  :op4 "Unity")
            :ord (o3 / ordinal-entity
                  :value 2))
      :location (h / here)
      :time (t / today))

                              :name (n3 / name
                                    :op1 "South"
                                    :op2 "Korea"))
                        :ARG2 (m / minister
                              :topic (f / foreign))))
            :ARG1 (r2 / resign-01
                  :ARG0 p
                  :ARG1-of (c2 / cause-01
                        :ARG0 (h2 / hire-01

                                    :poss p)
                              :ARG1 (p2 / person
                                    :ARG0-of (h3 / have-rel-role-91
                                          :ARG1 p
                                          :ARG2 (d / daughter)))
                              :mod (c3 / controversy))))))

            :value 1

                  :unit (y / year))))

# ::alignments
(a / and
      :op1 (a2 / accuse-01
            :ARG0 (c / country
                  :name (n / name
                        :op1 "Turkmenistan"))
            :ARG1 (c2 / country
                  :name (n2 / name
                        :op1 "Ukraine"))
            :ARG2 (f / fail-01
                  :ARG1 c2
                  :ARG2 (p / pay-off-02
                        :ARG0 c2
                        :ARG1 (d / debt
                              :poss c)
                        :ARG3 (d2 / deliver-01
                              :ARG0 c2
                              :ARG1 (g / gas
                                    :ARG1-of (n3 / natural-03)))))
            :time (d3 / date-entity
                  :weekday (s / sunday)))
      :op2 (w / warn-01
            :ARG0 c
            :ARG1 (j / jeopardize-01
                  :ARG0 f
                  :ARG1 (c3 / cooperate-01
                        :ARG0 c
                        :ARG1 c2
                        :ARG2 (s2 / sector
                              :mod (e / energy))))))

      :ARG0 (c / country

                  :ARG2 (c2 / country
                        :name (n / name

                                          :op1 "Africa")))
                        :ARG2-of (ii / include-91
                              :ARG1 (a2 / and
                                    :op1 (c4 / country
                                          :name (n3 / name
                                                :op1 "Little"
                                                :op2 "Rwanda"))
                                    :op2 (c5 / country
                                          :name (n4 / name
                                                :op1 "Burundi"))
                                    :op3 (c6 / country
                                          :name (n5 / name
                                                :op1 "Zaire")
                                          :mod (g / giant)
                                          :time (f2 / former))
                                    :op4 (c7 / country
                                          :name (n6 / name
                                                :op1 "Angola")
                                          :mod g))))))
      :direction e)
